lat bed sheet with side hems (100% cotton, tight weave)\n\n*\u2009Scissors\n\n*\u2009Measuring tape (or 8.5'\" x 11\" piece of paper to approximate)\n\n*\u2009Large paper clip (or other malleable metal strip like floral wire or pipe cleaner) to make the nose pinch.\n\n*\u2009Safety pins (or stapler)\n\nYour finished mask should look like this:\n\nYou can reuse the mask. Place it in boiling water for five minutes. After you turn off the heat, \"carefully remove the mask with tongs and place it on a clean paper towel.\" Schrock said in his video.", "source": {"uri": "marketwatch.com", "dataType": "news", "title": "MarketWatch"}, "authors": [{"uri": "elisabeth_buchwald@marketwatch.com", "name": "Elisabeth Buchwald", "type": "author", "isAgency": false}], "concepts": [{"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus", "type": "wiki", "score": 5, "label": {"eng": "Coronavirus"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgical_mask", "type": "wiki", "score": 5, "label": {"eng": "Surgical mask"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mask", "type": "wiki", "score": 5, "label": {"eng": "Mask"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_de_Blasio", "type": "person", "score": 4, "label": {"eng": "Bill de Blasio"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Do_it_yourself", "type": "wiki", "score": 4, "label": {"eng": "Do it yourself"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayor_of_New_York_City", "type": "wiki", "score": 4, "label": {"eng": "Mayor of New York City"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom", "type": "wiki", "score": 4, "label": {"eng": "Symptom"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virus", "type": "wiki", "score": 4, "label": {"eng": "Virus"}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States", "type": "loc", "score": 4, "label": {"eng": "United States"}, "location": {"type": "country", "label": {"eng": "United States"}}}, {"uri": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_distancing", "type": "wiki", "score": 3, "label": {"eng": "Social distancing"